As already pointed out in the comments, there is not an easy way to produce chained functions without specifically defining the input-output type for each of them and keeping the solution flexible.

A solution asks for a compromise by keeping the `Function` raw that would not enforce the types at the compile time and does not prevent runtime errors.

```java
private static Object flow(Object input, Function... functions) {
	Object temp = input;
	for (Function function : functions) {
		temp = function.apply(temp);
	}
	return temp;
}
```
Usage:
```java
