[&lt;kbd&gt;ONLINE DEMO&lt;/kbd&gt;][1]

### How does it work?

The function, [`YearMonth#toString`](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/time/YearMonth.html#toString--) returns a string in the format, `uuuu-MM`, the format I have used with the `DateTimeFormatterBuilder`. I have defaulted the [`ChronoField.DAY_OF_MONTH`](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/time/temporal/ChronoField.html#DAY_OF_MONTH) to 31, the maximum number of days a month can have, and this works for all months.

